cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a real-time collective anomaly detection model based on neural network learning and feature operating. It uses Long Short Term Memory Recurrent Neural Network (LSTM RNN) for prediction and anomaly detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with neural network learning. The paper also deals with network security, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of LSTM RNN also suggests the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves classification, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a new idea for detecting collective anomalies, which can be considered as a sub-topic of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
